# Static Dropdown Preload Flow (Using Map - Gender):

01. JSP me dropdown ke liye HashMap banaya jata hai:
    HashMap<String, String> map = new HashMap<>();

02. Map me static values add ki jati hain:
    map.put("Male", "Male");
    map.put("Female", "Female");

03. HTMLUtility.getList() method call hoti hai:
    HTMLUtility.getList("gender", bean.getGender(), map)

04. getList(name, selectedVal, map) method call hoti hai.

05. StringBuffer object banaya jata hai:
    <select name='gender'>

06. Default option add kiya jata hai:
    <option selected value=''>-------------Select-------------</option>

07. Map ke keys nikale jate hain:
    Set<String> keys = map.keySet();

08. Loop chalaya jata hai:
    for (String key : keys)

09. Har key ke liye:
    - val = map.get(key)

10. Check kiya jata hai:
    if (key.equals(selectedVal))

11. Agar selected value match karti hai:
    <option selected value='key'>val</option>

12. Agar match nahi karti:
    <option value='key'>val</option>

13. Loop complete hone ke baad:
    </select> close kiya jata hai

14. Final HTML dropdown string return hoti hai.

15. JSP me:
    returned HTML directly render hoti hai.

16. Final output:
    Static dropdown (Gender) user ko display hota hai.
